definition: body/life/oneself/personally/one's morality and conduct/the main part of a structure or body/pregnant/classifier for sets of clothes: suit, twinset/Kangxi radical 158
strong/powerful/better/slightly more than/vigorous/violent/best in their category, e.g. see 百強|百强[bai3 qiang2]
to force/to compel/to strive/to make an effort
Zhuang ethnic group of Guangxi, the PRC's second most numerous ethnic group

sentences.english: I have no cramps and I feel strong.
sentences.chinese: 我手腳沒有抽筋，我感到身強力壯。

sentences.english: I feel as well and strong as ever.
sentences.chinese: 我覺得身強力壯一如以往。

sentences.english: A strong man is not willing to be a loafer or sponger.
sentences.chinese: 身強力壯的人誰也不願吃閒飯。

sentences.english: As a result, we can become strong-bodied.
sentences.chinese: 這樣我們就能身強力壯。

sentences.english: Boys a year older than the Qin-fen, but also able-bodied, very domineering.
sentences.chinese: 男孩比秦奮大一歲，又身強力壯，很霸道。

sentences.english: Although he is getting along, he is still strong and lusty.
sentences.chinese: 他雖然上了年紀，但還是身強力壯。

sentences.english: The heavyset man over there is my uncle.
sentences.chinese: 那兒的那個身強力壯的男人是我叔叔。

sentences.english: Like charges to stick, chicken, and did not take wives, all hit others physique.
sentences.chinese: 喜歡刺槍使棒，身強力壯，不取妻室，終日打熬筋骨。

sentences.english: None but a strong man could have lifted it.
sentences.chinese: 只有身強力壯的人能舉得起它。

sentences.english: It took three strong men to hold him down.
sentences.chinese: 三個身強力壯的男子才把他給按住了。
